---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="About | Mind"
      description="Learn more about the Mind project"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main class="w-full max-w-[800px] mx-auto p-4">
      <div class="mb-12 border-b-4 border-black pb-8">
        <h1
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-mono uppercase mb-4 leading-none"
        >
          > About_Mind_
        </h1>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2>What is Mind?</h2>
          <p class="font-body text-gray-dark leading-relaxed">
            Mind is a living collection of ideas, thoughts, and evolving
            concepts. It's a space where projects are documented not as
            finished products, but as journeys of exploration.
          </p>
          <p class="font-body text-gray-dark leading-relaxed">
            Each "idea" is a chronological record of thoughts as they emerge,
            develop, and transform over time. Think of it as a digital garden
            where ideas grow organically.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2>How It Works</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 font-body text-gray-dark">
            <div class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-mono uppercase mb-2">Ideas</h3>
              <p>
                Each idea represents a topic, project, or area of exploration.
                Ideas contain thoughts, tags, and a changelog of their
                evolution.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-mono uppercase mb-2">Thoughts</h3>
              <p>
                Thoughts are individual entries within an idea, added
                chronologically. They can be reflections, notes, learnings, or
                developments.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-mono uppercase mb-2">Tags</h3>
              <p>
                Hashtags organize ideas by topic, making it easy to find related
                concepts and explore connections.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-mono uppercase mb-2">Changelog</h3>
              <p>
                Every change to an idea is tracked, creating a history of how
                the concept evolved over time.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2>Philosophy</h2>
          <blockquote
            class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 italic text-gray font-body"
          >
            "Knowledge is not static. It's a living, breathing thing that grows
            through exploration, reflection, and connection."
          </blockquote>
          <p class="font-body text-gray-dark leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Mind embraces the imperfect, the evolving, and the incomplete. It's
            a rejection of the pressure to only share "finished" work, and an
            embrace of learning in public.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2>Part of the Ecosystem</h2>
          <p class="font-body text-gray-dark leading-relaxed">
            Mind is part of the <a
              href="https://hecarrieswater.com"
              class="text-accent hover:underline">He Carries Water</a
            > project — a collection of interconnected tools and spaces for thinking,
            creating, and sharing.
          </p>
        </section>

        <div
          class="border-2 border-black bg-accent/10 p-6 text-center shadow-custom"
        >
          <p class="font-mono text-sm mb-4">
            Ready to explore ideas in progress?
          </p>
          <a
            href="/"
            class="inline-block px-6 py-3 border-2 border-black bg-accent text-white font-mono uppercase font-bold hover:bg-accent-dark transition-all shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_black] hover:translate-x-[4px] hover:translate-y-[4px] hover:shadow-none no-underline"
          >
            Browse Ideas →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .shadow-custom {
    box-shadow: 4px 4px 0px 0px var(--color-black);
  }
</style>
